    "description": "Files whose Distributed Link Tracker metadata reveals they ORIGINATED ON ANOTHER MACHINE. When a Windows host first opens a file, it stamps the file's LNK with the local MachineID + MAC. If that ID doesn't match the host where the jump-list entry was found, the file traveled between machines (USB / network share / file transfer / Resilient Sharepoint copy / etc.). This is one of the most reliable forensic signals for tracking file movement across systems.",
